---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout title="Fluidity Character Framework">
  <div class="mb-6">
    <a href="/" class="text-cyan-400 hover:text-cyan-300 text-sm"><- Return to Mission Control</a>
  </div>
  
  <header class="mb-8 border-b border-slate-800 pb-4">
    <h1 class="text-3xl md:text-4xl font-bold text-slate-100 uppercase">Fluidity Character Framework</h1>
    <p class="text-emerald-400 mt-2 text-sm">// Unreal Engine 5 | C++ | Mover Plugin</p>
  </header>

  <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-3 gap-8">
    
    <div class="col-span-1 md:col-span-2 space-y-8">
      <section>
        <h2 class="text-xl text-slate-100 mb-3 border-b border-slate-800 pb-1">// The Problem</h2>
        <p class="text-sm leading-relaxed text-slate-400">
          Standard character controllers often lack the modularity required for complex, state-driven gameplay. The goal was to engineer a robust locomotion system that separates input handling from state logic, preventing monolithic, unmaintainable C++ classes.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-xl text-slate-100 mb-3 border-b border-slate-800 pb-1">// The Architecture</h2>
        <p class="text-sm leading-relaxed text-slate-400 mb-4">
          Built natively in C++ by extending the experimental Mover plugin. The architecture utilizes a finite state machine (FSM) tailored for high-performance animation blending and precise collision predictions.
        </p>
        
        <div class="bg-slate-950 border border-slate-800 rounded p-4 overflow-x-auto">
          <pre class="text-xs text-slate-300"><code><span class="text-slate-500">// FFluidityCharacterState.h</span>
UCLASS()
class UFluidityMovementComponent : public UMoverComponent
{
    GENERATED_BODY()

protected:
    virtual void OnRegister() override;
    void HandleStateTransition(EFluidityState NewState);
    
    UPROPERTY(EditAnywhere, Category = "Locomotion Metrics")
    float MaxPredictedSpeed;
};</code></pre>
        </div>
      </section>
    </div>
    
    <div class="space-y-6">
      <div class="bg-slate-900 border border-slate-800 p-5 rounded">
        <h3 class="text-cyan-400 text-sm font-bold uppercase mb-2">Technical Bottleneck</h3>
        <p class="text-xs text-slate-400 leading-relaxed">
          Initial implementations resulted in state desynchronization during rapid input buffering. Resolved by decoupling the animation update tick from the physics step, ensuring frame-independent input polling.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="bg-slate-900 border border-slate-800 p-5 rounded">
        <h3 class="text-slate-100 text-sm font-bold uppercase mb-2">Key Features</h3>
        <ul class="text-xs text-slate-400 space-y-2 list-disc pl-4">
          <li>Custom C++ Header structures.</li>
          <li>Frame-independent input polling.</li>
          <li>Modular component design.</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>

  </div>
</Layout>